entries.title: Former Labor MP Tania Mihailuk accused by Bankstown mayor Khal Asfour of misusing ratepayer funds
entries.description: Ex NSW Labor MP Tania Mihailuk is accused of using ratepayer funds to buy slabs of beer, vodka, Chinese meals and chicken nuggets by her former party colleague Khal Asfour.

entries.title: Townsville boy Andre Daisy dies from meningitis after sore tummy, headache symptoms in Brisbane
entries.description: The devastated family of a five-year-old boy who died from severe meningitis believed the little boy had a 'tummy bug' after complaining about a headache and a sore stomach.

entries.title: Shoppers could use digital currency dubbed 'Britcoin' instead of cash
entries.description: The proposals would create a 'digital pound' issued by the Bank, accessed through digital wallets and interchangeable with cash and bank deposits.

entries.title: Australia will give $10 million in humanitarian assistance to to help Turkey
entries.description: Australia will give $10 million in humanitarian assistance to help response efforts following Turkey's devastating earthquake.

entries.title: Former Newcastle star Christian Atsu rescued from rubble of building after Turkey earthquake
entries.description: Former Chelsea and Newcastle star Christian Atsu is alive in the rubble of a destroyed building after Monday's 7.8-magnitude earthquake in Turkey, according to reports.

entries.title: Rishi Sunak is to announce mini-reshuffle TODAY
entries.description: Trade minister Greg Hands and Business Secretary Grant Shapps are being touted as potential replacements.

entries.title: Ladies of The View decide GOP played into China's hands by criticizing Biden for NOT shooting down
entries.description: Some of the ladies of 'The View' criticized Republicans for bashing President Biden's response to the spy balloon incident while others agreed with his handling of the crisis.

entries.title: Fallen TV host Andrew O'Keefe confidently arrives for court with his fly down
entries.description: Dressed in a stone linen suit and bright striped tie, former TV presenter Andrew O'Keefe appeared polished as he arrived at a Sydney court on Tuesday - except for one small detail.

entries.title: Yellowstone could wrap at the end of this season
entries.description: Kevin Costner reportedly asked Paramount Network executives to let him spend only one week filming the second half of Yellowstone's fifth season, but network executives refused.

entries.title: Boost for families as experts forecast energy bills will be £600 less than feared
entries.description: The average household will pay £2,400 in 2023-24, down from the £3,000 forecast by the Government last autumn, according to the Resolution Foundation.

entries.title: Specialist diving teams prepare to join police for second day of searching for Nicola Bulley
entries.description: Peter Faulding, founder of the Specialist Group International search and rescue organisation said rescue efforts would continue on Tuesday after his team failed to locate Nicola Bulley on Monday.

entries.title: Fury as Rishi Sunak 'rules out increase in military spending' despite war in Ukraine
entries.description: Rishi Sunak appears to have ruled out an increase in defence spending despite Britain's commitment to the war in Ukraine.

entries.title: TikToker Dragon Hunter, Julian O'Bayrd in Brisbane hospital after touching blue sea dragons | video
entries.description: Brisbane marine expert Julian O'Bayd, better known on TikTok as the Dragon Hunter filmed himself handling one of the ocean's most beautiful but dangerous creatures.

entries.title: Lord Frost accuses peers of trying to 'block the spirit of Brexit' over bid to scrap EU laws
entries.description: Boris Johnson's Brexit negotiator, Lord Frost, said  the decision was crucial to extricate 'ourselves properly and fully from the EU legal framework'. But anti-Brexit peers have called it 'reckless'.

entries.title: Alex Salmond claims Nicola Sturgeon has 'thrown away' years of campaigning for Scottish independence
entries.description: In footage posted on Twitter, Mr Salmond said he had assumed that the leaders of the nationalist movement 'well understood' the need to win over 'every part and section' of Scotland.

entries.title: Beat that! Couple finds ten yolks in four eggs while making a fry-up... at odds of one in 11billion
entries.description: Chris Tulley, 26, found the amazingly rare eggs while preparing breakfast at his home in Sheffield, cracking open four eggs to find the incredibly rare occurrence.

entries.title: George Santos denies former aide's claims he sexually harassed him
entries.description: Despite the latest in a string of public relations crises for Santos, he found time to partake in a tradition for lawmakers on Capitol Hill by formally announcing his guest for Biden's State of the Union.

entries.title: FBI will search Mike Pence's Indiana home for classified documents in DAYS
entries.description: Vice President Mike Pence's Indiana home will be searched for more classified documents 'in a matter of days,' NBC News reported Monday .

entries.title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: The dangerous folly of stinting on defence
entries.description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: There are many onerous obligations on any government, from funding public health and education to maintaining law and order.

entries.title: Welsh school is rapped for letting pupils speak too much English
entries.description: Inspectors found many of the 331 pupils at the primary 'turn to English naturally' when chatting and were not given enough chances to 'celebrate their Welshness'.

entries.title: Could passports backlog be over? Hope for holidaymakers as processing time is down to three weeks
entries.description: Delays were widespread last year when demand to renew passports surged following the Covid pandemic but 97 per cent of applications are now being completed in three weeks.

entries.title: Jails are set to run out of space in two weeks with prisoners set be housed in police cells instead
entries.description: Prisoners will be housed in police cells instead of prisons in the North West and West Midlands, after the Ministry of Justice gave forces a fortnight's notice to make preparations.

entries.title: Charles Bronson could be free from prison in months as he confirms in letter to his 'long lost son'
entries.description: In a letter to his 'long-lost son', Charles Bronson, 70, wrote that his historic public parole hearing has been set for March 6. The violent prisoner could be freed after spending nearly 30 years in prison.

entries.title: Mother who 'loved being outside' is trampled to death by a herd of cows
entries.description: Kathy McKellar had been staying in a holiday cottage in Lancashire last September with her beloved cockapoo Archie when she was found dead in a field after being trampled by cows.

entries.title: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: Woes of George VI's coronation
entries.description: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: King Charles studies the near-calamities of his grandfather George VI's 1937 crowning, including the Archbishop of Canterbury placing the crown back to front.

entries.title: The Capitol fence returns for the State of the Union address
entries.description: The Capitol fence was reinstalled in advance of Tuesday night's State of the Union address, annoying D.C.'s Democratic rep but delighting some conservatives

entries.title: Biden STILL refuses to accept responsibility for classified documents debacle
entries.description: President Joe Biden answered in the negative Monday when asked if he should take any blame for mishandling classified information.

entries.title: Excited Maryborough, Queensland teen camps outside new 7-Eleven all night
entries.description: A teenager was so excited about a new 7-Eleven store coming to his regional town he camped out all night to make sure he was first in line when it opened its door.

entries.title: State of the Union: Republicans urge Biden to address Chinese spy balloon, federal spending, border
entries.description: The president will be delivering his first speech to a divided Congress, tasked with bringing a unifying message to a Republican-controlled House and a Democrat-held Senate.

entries.title: Vanessa Feltz defiantly speaks out after split from fiancé Ben Ofoedu
entries.description: Vanessa Feltz, 60, has said her heart snapped into 'a million pieces' after she split from her ex-fiancé Ben Ofoedu amid claims he cheated.

entries.title: Darko 'Dougie' Desic, the fugitive who surrendered 30 years after a jail break gets permanent visa
entries.description: Darko 'Dougie' Desic, who escaped from Grafton Prison in 1992 after being jailed for growing dope, is a free man and no longer has to check over his shoulder.

entries.title: King Charles shares message on New Zealand national holiday while snubbing Australia
entries.description: The UK monarch sent over his warm wishes over to mark Waitangi Day on Monday with the letter written in English and the native te reo language.

entries.title: Watch as King's Guard shouts 'get off'!' at tourist
entries.description: The woman wearing a white coat, navy skirt and black boots can be seen smiling and happy as she tries to pose for a picture before grabbing the horse's reins.

entries.title: Dominic Raab tried to get Cabinet rival fired after disagreement over human rights, source says
entries.description: The Deputy Prime Minister was claimed to have been enraged by an article Sir Robert Buckland, a former justice secretary, wrote in summer last year criticising Mr Raab's plans for a British Bill of Rights.

entries.title: Throwing money at the NHS is not the solution to crisis in the health service
entries.description: General Sir Gordon Messenger said the NHS urgently needs improvements in management, without which extra funding will be wasted.

entries.title: Fiona Bruce broke accuracy rules over general election 'show of hands' on Question Time
entries.description: After investigating a complaint about the episode which aired in October, the corporation admitted her 'summary' of audience opinion 'fell short of the BBC's standards of accuracy'.

entries.title: 'It's time to get to work': Kevin McCarthy turns up the heat on Biden to negotiate debt limit
entries.description: Kevin McCarthy turned up the heat on President Biden to 'sit down and negotiate' on the debt ceiling on the eve before the president will deliver his State of the Union Address.

entries.title: Ken Bruce fans could get their radio fix by PAYING to listen to his show on new station
entries.description: The commercial station is hoping a new ad-free premium subscription service will entice disaffected fans to follow the 72-year-old star from Radio 2.

entries.title: Perth mother-of-three sleeping in her car with kids amid Western Australia's rental crisis
entries.description: A single mother has resorted to sleeping in her car with her three children as Australia's rental crisis leaves thousands without a home.

entries.title: Tony Abbott joins UK's Global Warming Policy Foundation, a thinktank sceptical of climate change
entries.description: The ex-politician, 65, has signed up to the Board of Trustees of the London-based Global Warming Policy Foundation, a thinktank that challenges 'damaging and harmful' climate change policies.

entries.title: ABC Media Watch host condemns his own network for Alice Springs report
entries.description: ABC issued a grovelling apology earlier this week and admitted it had provided 'incomplete' coverage of the Save Alice Springs meeting.

entries.title: WA: Witness reports spotting GIANT bull shark day before 16-year-old girl killed
entries.description: A huge bull shark was seen on Perth's Swan River the day before teenager Stella Berry was killed by a shark - but was only reported the day after her death.

entries.title: Did Trump's defense secretary KNOW Chinese spy balloons flew over US but 'decide not to tell him'?
entries.description: Rep. Mike Waltz floated the idea on Monday that the Pentagon was aware of Chinese balloons drifting across the country during Donald Trump's time in office but did not tell the White House.

entries.title: Australians are falsely claiming to be Aboriginal to seek benefits, historian says
entries.description: Prominent Aboriginal Australians and an amateur historian have hit out at the rising number of Aussies falsely claiming they have Indigenous to cash in on benefits.

entries.title: Neurosurgeon Charlie Teo to face more complaints at disciplinary hearing next week
entries.description: The Health Care Complaints Commission has received complaints alleging unsatisfactory professional conduct by the controversial Sydney neurosurgeon.

entries.title: Britain sends 76 rescuers to join international aid effort for earthquake-hit Turkey
entries.description: A team of search and rescue specialists, with life-saving equipment and rescue dogs, was due to arrive in Gaziantep last night.

entries.title: Getting his Minnie's worth! Ron DeSantis seizes control of Disney's Reedy Creek Improvement District
entries.description: Ron DeSantis is escalating the battle against Reedy Creek by taking full control of overseeing Disney's self-governing special tax district encompassing the nearly 40 miles of Walt Disney World Resort.

entries.title: Banks are leaving open doors for scammers with flaws in both web and app security
entries.description: A study by Which? found that several banks were missing basic protections, and fuelling a multi-billion-pound fraud epidemic.

entries.title: Chilling 911 dispatch describes how 'overmedicated' midwife mom Lindsay Clancy cut her own wrists
entries.description: The audio reveals her extensive injuries, including cuts on her wrists and lacerations, which she is believed to have inflicted on herself before jumping from a window of her home.

entries.title: Woman charged with MURDER after baby is found dead in a Melbourne home
entries.description: A woman has been charged with murder after a toddler was found dead in Melbourne's western suburbs.

entries.title: OpenPay buy now, pay later firm collapses: Bunnings, Kogan customers in lurch over tech company fail
entries.description: Australian buy now, pay later company OpenPay has gone under after a disastrous three months saw the company lose $18million.

entries.title: Harrowing video footage shows the scale of destruction in Turkey and Syria following earthquakes
entries.description: The most devastating earthquake to hit the region since 1939 erupted under their feet before dawn, wreaking a trail of utter chaos that stretched beyond 200 miles across Turkey and Syria
